  <Properties>
    <contentGrid>
      <Value><![CDATA[{
  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "f170b29c-338f-4ab8-a5c4-f72c90826f69",
      "key": "800495c0-e5cf-4877-a0a1-2a600ec32d9d",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "c345e5ce-768f-47e0-968a-e7859dbe0b07",
      "key": "e9eb741a-cfda-4eed-92c0-138785f0abc9",
      "values": []
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "e94b4c4f-2415-4af7-bac2-0a7405864cfe",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "What It Does"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Creates an expandable and collapsible FAQ section using Bootstrap accordion"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe FAQs feature lets content editors build a list of questions and answers that render as a Bootstrap accordion. Each question appears as a clickable header that expands to reveal the answer, and clicking another question collapses the previous one.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis is a common pattern for support pages, product documentation, and any content where users need to scan through multiple topics without being overwhelmed by all the answers at once.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "The accordion uses Bootstrap\u0027s flush variant for a cleaner look without outer borders."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "d5bfea49-0733-48ff-9ee0-d83c01a4cbf4",
      "key": "f70abdb6-7a08-4de3-a682-f175cbe59c87",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureTitle",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "How It Works"
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureDescription",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "A Block List of question/answer pairs rendered as a Bootstrap accordion"
        },
        {
          "alias": "richTextContent",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "blocks": {
              "contentData": [],
              "settingsData": [],
              "expose": [],
              "Layout": {}
            },
            "markup": "\u003Cp\u003EThe feature uses a Block List property (\u003Ccode\u003EfeaturePropertyFAQs\u003C/code\u003E) containing question/answer element types. Each element has a \u003Ccode\u003EfeaturePropertyFAQsQuestion\u003C/code\u003E textbox and a \u003Ccode\u003EfeaturePropertyFAQsAnswer\u003C/code\u003E textarea.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe view iterates through the Block List items and renders each as a Bootstrap accordion item. The accordion uses \u003Ccode\u003Edata-bs-parent\u003C/code\u003E to ensure only one answer is visible at a time \u2014 opening a new question automatically closes the previous one.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnique IDs for the accordion and its items are generated from the block\u0027s \u003Ccode\u003EKey\u003C/code\u003E property, ensuring multiple FAQ blocks on the same page don\u0027t conflict.\u003C/p\u003E"
          }
        },
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFeatureSummary",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": "Editors manage FAQs through a simple Block List \u2014 just add question/answer pairs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "b4148cb6-f6d9-42f9-a6df-3aa3f31ea68e",
      "key": "16f664c3-a3ac-48e7-90e9-b31f953173d9",
      "values": [
        {
          "alias": "featurePropertyFAQs",
          "culture": null,
          "editorAlias": null,
          "segment": null,
          "value": {
            "contentData": [
              {
                "contentTypeKey": "bd6fd684-5515-46eb-816a-685bbb312219",
                "key": "8c9cefe6-9fc2-4a96-8d61-c036c64ec5c2",
                "values": [
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsQuestion",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "Why should I use Umbraco?"
                  },
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsAnswer",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "If you\u0027re looking for a flexible and user-friendly CMS, you might want to check out Umbraco. Umbraco is an open-source platform that lets you create and manage any kind of website, from blogs to e-commerce. You can customize it to suit your needs, and it has a vibrant community of developers and users who are always ready to help. Plus, it\u0027s free to use and easy to learn. What\u0027s not to love?\n"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "contentTypeKey": "bd6fd684-5515-46eb-816a-685bbb312219",
                "key": "11e06ac7-2818-438f-a3d0-bb61c2f0e7cc",
                "values": [
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsQuestion",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "Why should I use Bootstrap?"
                  },
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsAnswer",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "Bootstrap is awesome, you know? It\u0027s like a magic tool that makes your web design super easy and fast. You don\u0027t have to worry about writing tons of CSS or JavaScript code, because Bootstrap has it all ready for you. You just use their classes and components, and boom, you have a responsive and beautiful website. Plus, Bootstrap is compatible with all browsers and devices, so you don\u0027t have to deal with annoying bugs or glitches. Trust me, Bootstrap will save you a lot of time and hassle. You should definitely give it a try!\n"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "contentTypeKey": "bd6fd684-5515-46eb-816a-685bbb312219",
                "key": "d5d241ad-1f87-4ca8-8460-7482f14c81f7",
                "values": [
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsQuestion",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "Why should I use Umbootstrap?"
                  },
                  {
                    "alias": "featurePropertyFAQsAnswer",
                    "culture": null,
                    "editorAlias": null,
                    "segment": null,
                    "value": "Hey, you might be wondering why you should use Umbootstrap for your next web project. Well, let me tell you, it\u0027s awesome! Umbootstrap is a sleek, intuitive, and powerful front-end framework for faster and easier web development. It has everything you need to create responsive, modern, and beautiful websites that work on any device. Plus, it\u0027s super easy to customize and extend with your own code and plugins. Trust me, once you try Umbootstrap, you\u0027ll never go back to anything else!\n"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ],
            "settingsData": [],
            "expose": [
